==English==
===Etymology===
Suggested as having an Australian aboriginal origin, but that seems unlikely.  One possibility is ''[[bung]]'' (elder brother) in the [[Jakarta]] dialect of [[Indonesian]].  (Reference: [[w:R. M. W. Dixon|R. M. W. Dixon]], Australian Aboriginal Words'', Oxford University Press, 1990, ISBN 0-19-553099-3, page 165.)
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{slang}} (''very insulting'') An Australian [[aborigine]].  Also applied to idengenous people of [[New Guinea]], [[Malaysia]], etc.
